reviewText: Kept my grandson happy for the 8 hour car ride while traveling to our vacation spot

Two of the DVDs in this collection are duplicates of those included in Curious George: Monkey Collection - Volume 1. I would have known this if I'd read the descriptions more closely, but unfortunately one doesn't always have the luxury of time with toddlers around. I'm very disappointed with this purchase.
My daughter loved this! Very Satisfied!
Love watching, remembering when all I had was the books.  Very good.

My children adore Curious George, but be forewarned that Collection #2 contains TWO of the same discs that are sold in Monkey Collection #1 on Amazon.  We purchased both, and I'm sorely disappointed in the price I paid for duplicates.

If your child is at the age when he or she is easily frightened by some videowe do not consider frightening in the least, these are great ways to calm the child down, make them laugh, and retell the story after they have seen it. They are all about solving problems by observation (unlike the older Curious George, which were always getting into trouble and finding the way to make it come out all right). Our son ansorbs the problem-solving lessons like a sponge.
